        explain: "The parser expected an opening brace `{` to begin a block expression (fn body, if/else arm, while body, struct/enum body). Without it, the parser cannot tell where the body starts and may silently absorb the next item into the surrounding context. Stage1 punch list Gap 5 — added so block-open mismatches surface as a precise S0 diagnostic instead of a downstream cascade. Note: braces are escaped from the message template here because `compiler/diag/builder.hexa::_interpolate` treats raw `{...}` as a placeholder boundary.",
        fix_it_kind: FixItKind::Insert
    },
    DiagSpec {
